						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 1/8 <hi rend="italic">s11ēy (vēli)</hi> of land to provide for offerings during the <hi rend="italic">ardhayāma</hi> service, to god Śrīkuḍittiṭṭai-Perumāḷ at Avaninārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> and <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> on the northern bank of the river, by <hi rend="bold">Dōṇaya-Kramavittaṉ of Koṇḍampatti</hi> (a member) of the <hi rend="italic">āḷungaṇam</hi> of the village. This writing is early and the record may be one of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
